node.text:
Dear Instagram, 
@mosseri @creators ..
(Please tag them in the comments)

I’m writing this because again, I have been banned from showing up on hashtags, banned from monetization and banned from brand content tagging. My notifications don’t go out to people when I go live, and I am not showing up in search bars. NO ONE new can see my account. 

I have never broken any community guidelines. I post awareness about mental health, which sometimes includes Suicide awareness and prevention. This is important and shouldn’t result in me being banned. My content is to help people. But these constant bans and flagging my account for weeks, (no idea if this one is permanent) isn’t fair as I’m trying so hard to make a difference here. My platform has 380+ followers who need my content. 

I have never and will never break any guidelines on here, my page is purely to break the stigma of mental health and help anyone who is suffering to feel less alone. Please please unflag my account.

Hannah.
